COMMITTEE OF THE WHOLE/FLOOR
BILL NO. 36-0125
Thirty-Sixth Legislature of the Virgin Islands
July 23, 2025
An act amending title 3 Virgin Islands Code, chapters 25 and 27 relating to simultaneous
payment of non-legislative annuities to serving members of the Legislature of the Virgin
Islands
PROPOSED BY: Senator Milton E. Potter, by Request of the Governor
1 WHEREAS, retirees who return to government service, including those elected as
2 governor or lieutenant governor, are not allowed to collect both a salary and a pension under
3 Virgin Islands law;
4 WHEREAS, current law creates a special exception for members of the Legislature of
5 the Virgin Islands, allowing them to collect both a retirement annuity for past government
6 service and their legislative salary;
7 WHEREAS, this special exception for legislators is unfair to other government retirees
8 returning to service, and undermines public trust in the government retirement system;
9 WHEREAS, this practice of is fiscally irresponsible while the Government Employees
10 Retirement System is severely underfunded and the Territory faces serious financial challenges;
11 and
12 WHEREAS, repealing this special exception will bring consistency to the law, support
13 fairness and help to protect the long-term health of the public pension system; Now, Therefore,

2
1 Be it enacted by the Legislature of the Virgin Islands:
2 SECTION 1. Title 3 Virgin Islands Code is amended as follows:
3 (a) In chapter 25, section 714, by striking subsection (g) and redesignating the
4 remaining subsections accordingly; and
5 (b) In chapter 27, section 763 by striking subsection (g) and redesignating the
6 remaining subsections accordingly.
7 SECTION 2. This act takes effect 90 days after enactment.
8 BILL SUMMARY
9 This bill amends title 3 Virgin Islands Code, chapter 25 and 27, by striking subsections
10 relating to the simultaneous payment of non-legislative annuities to serving members of the
11 Legislature of the Virgin Islands.
